## Overview
Kahoot is an online game-based learning platform used to create interactive games for sessions.

## Purpose
To bring fun and engagement to session dynamics, while also evaluating participants' knowledge on specific topics.

## How it works
Users can create interactive games using Kahoot's platform, which can be played in real-time. Games can be used to break the ice, set the scene, or evaluate participants' knowledge.

## Requirements
Digital skills are necessary to effectively use Kahoot for R&D purposes.

## Reflections
Consider the context and audience when creating games, and ensure that they align with the session's goals and objectives.

## Related methods (if any)
Citizen Science and play-based methods can be used in conjunction with Kahoot to enhance engagement and participation.
